INT. DAWES BARN - NIGHT (WEDNESDAY)

The barn, half empty still. Where the simulator stood: the same clean rectangle of dust. Cricket sits at the workbench with just the radio now, no panel, no couch, no window. He keys the mic.

CRICKET:
Net's open.

DUTCH (FILTERED):
Copy.

STITCH (FILTERED):
Copy.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
About time.

A silence on the net that isn't the usual silence.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
I did two years on a boomer off Adak listening for Soviet screws, so men like Earl could keep a barn a Russian couldn't touch. And a fella in a zip-up vest walks in with a sticker gun.

STITCH (FILTERED):
Say the word, Gunny. You've been chewing on it since Tuesday.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
Commies. That's the word. Don't care what flag they're flying over the building. That's what they are, and we used to know what to do about that.

DUTCH (FILTERED):
(quiet, to no one in particular)
NASA was going to scrap that trainer in seventy-five. Cut it for aluminum. I drove a horse trailer to Houston and asked a supply captain if anybody'd miss it. He said the paperwork was eight months backed up, and if the truck showed up empty, that's what the truck would show.
(beat)
Fifty years I kept government property safe for the government. They sent a man to take it back like I stole it.

CRICKET:
And do what. Burn something down. I've got a grandson.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
Nobody said burn anything down.

CRICKET:
Then what did you say.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
Compliance office closes at five. Empty gravel lot out back, faces the highway. Fourth of July's been illegal going on seven months now — no sale, no discharge, not even in your own yard. I've still got four cases of good mortar shells from before the ban.

STITCH (FILTERED):
Big loud middle finger. Nobody gets hurt. We're home by ten.

CRICKET:
That's a federal building.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
It's a strip mall with a flagpole, Earl.

CRICKET:
(flat)
No.

Silence on the net.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
No, meaning you want to think on it, or—

CRICKET:
No, meaning no. I've got a grandson who still thinks I hung the moon. Not explaining a courtroom to him. Count me out.

A longer silence. Dutch doesn't say anything at all.

STITCH (FILTERED):
(quiet)
...Copy that.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
Fine. Rest of us, then. Friday.

CRICKET:
Do what you're going to do. Just don't tell me about it after.

GUNNY (FILTERED):
Copy.

DUTCH (FILTERED):
(after a moment)
Copy.

Cricket keys off. Doesn't say anything else. Sits a while with his hand still on the dead mic, the dust rectangle in front of him where the trainer used to stand.

CUT TO:
